---
import Main from '../layouts/main.astro'
---

<Main title='Method'>
  <div class="bg-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl py-24 sm:py-32 sm:px-2 lg:px-4">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-4 lg:max-w-none">
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-purple-500">From Idea to Continuous Excellence</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 sm:text-4xl">
            You have an idea!
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-gray-500">
            What next? How will your product vision to your developers? How do you make sure the final delivery serves your vision? Here is our method to figuring that out.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="relative mt-24">
          <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center" aria-hidden="true">
            <div class="w-full border-t border-gray-300"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="relative flex justify-center">
            <span class="bg-white px-3 text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Product Discovery</span>
          </div>
        </div>
  
        <div class="mt-10 space-y-16 pt-10 sm:mt-8 sm:pt-8">
          <div class="flex flex-col-reverse lg:grid lg:grid-cols-12 lg:items-center lg:gap-x-8">
            <div class="mt-6 lg:col-span-5 lg:mt-0 xl:col-span-4">
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-medium text-purple-600">Scoping</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">Product discovery process begins with scoping. This process is designed to answer the question of <strong>"What are we building?"</strong>. This process will ensure all stakeholders are on the same page before investing time into expensive development and engineering work.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex-auto lg:col-span-7 xl:col-span-8">
              <div class="aspect-w-16 aspect-h-9 overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-gray-100">
                <img src="https://tailwindui.com/img/ecommerce-images/product-feature-04-detail-03.jpg" alt="Printed photo of bag being tossed into the sky on top of grass." class="object-cover object-center">
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
  
          <div class="flex flex-col-reverse lg:grid lg:grid-cols-12 lg:items-center lg:gap-x-8">
            <div class="mt-6 lg:col-span-5 lg:mt-0 xl:col-span-4">
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-medium text-purple-600">Wireframing / Flow</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">Ensuring that all the stakeholders understand the same things are being built. In this part we begin to work on the flow of each of the key processes in the system.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex-auto lg:col-span-7 xl:col-span-8">
              <div class="aspect-w-16 aspect-h-9 overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-gray-100">
                <img src="https://tailwindui.com/img/ecommerce-images/product-feature-04-detail-01.jpg" alt="Double stitched black canvas hook loop." class="object-cover object-center">
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex flex-col-reverse lg:grid lg:grid-cols-12 lg:items-center lg:gap-x-8">
            <div class="mt-6 lg:col-span-5 lg:mt-0 xl:col-span-4">
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-medium text-purple-600">UI / UX</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">Once everyone can agree on a given flow, the next step is to make something which will help depict how the product is going to function from a user's perspective. This is where user experience design comes in. The UI design will determine how the product will look and feel, what color schemes it will use and so on and so forth.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex-auto lg:col-span-7 xl:col-span-8">
              <div class="aspect-w-16 aspect-h-9 overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-gray-100">
                <img src="https://tailwindui.com/img/ecommerce-images/product-feature-04-detail-01.jpg" alt="Double stitched black canvas hook loop." class="object-cover object-center">
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="relative">
            <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center" aria-hidden="true">
              <div class="w-full border-t border-gray-300"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="relative flex justify-center">
              <span class="bg-white px-3 text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Solution Design</span>
            </div>
          </div>
  
          <div class="flex flex-col-reverse lg:grid lg:grid-cols-12 lg:items-center lg:gap-x-8">
            <div class="mt-6 lg:col-span-5 lg:mt-0 xl:col-span-4">
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-medium text-purple-600">Architecture</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">This is where we draw out the flow of all the <strong>components that are necessary</strong>. We start to write out some processes on diagrams, even draw about any <strong>API endpoints</strong>, <strong>entity relationship diagrams</strong> that may be needed for a given feature set. This is the blueprint the software engineers will reference. It also gives the developer the opportunity to aks questions, ensure they have clarity before the execution.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex-auto lg:col-span-7 xl:col-span-8">
              <div class="aspect-w-16 aspect-h-9 overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-gray-100">
                <img src="https://tailwindui.com/img/ecommerce-images/product-feature-04-detail-02.jpg" alt="Black canvas body with chrome zipper and key ring." class="object-cover object-center">
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
  
          <div class="flex flex-col-reverse lg:grid lg:grid-cols-12 lg:items-center lg:gap-x-8">
            <div class="mt-6 lg:col-span-5 lg:mt-0 xl:col-span-4">
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-medium text-purple-600">Development</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">Finally once the blueprint has been agreed upon by everyone in the whole flow, all the way from business team, design, all the way to engineering. The development process begins. The development process happens on the code repository. Peer review, writing tests, writing maintainable code that is easy to read and follow as a natural part of development are things we believe are critical to the success of the project.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex-auto lg:col-span-7 xl:col-span-8">
              <div class="aspect-w-16 aspect-h-9 overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-gray-100">
                <img src="https://tailwindui.com/img/ecommerce-images/product-feature-04-detail-01.jpg" alt="Double stitched black canvas hook loop." class="object-cover object-center">
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="relative">
            <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center" aria-hidden="true">
              <div class="w-full border-t border-gray-300"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="relative flex justify-center">
              <span class="bg-white px-3 text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Product Delivery</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex flex-col-reverse lg:grid lg:grid-cols-12 lg:items-center lg:gap-x-8">
            <div class="mt-6 lg:col-span-5 lg:mt-0 xl:col-span-4">
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-medium text-purple-600">Continuous Excellence</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">All the development work that is done goes through a process called continuous integration and delivery. This is where, once changes are merged by the engineers they go through a UAT process. This allows the stakeholders to review the progress of the work on a regular basis. Finally once the stakeholder is happy they can decide when to ship the final version to the end-user. Since active software products don't 'finish'. When new feedback comes in from the user, the whole process is repeated again.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex-auto lg:col-span-7 xl:col-span-8">
              <div class="aspect-w-16 aspect-h-9 overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-gray-100">
                <img src="https://tailwindui.com/img/ecommerce-images/product-feature-04-detail-01.jpg" alt="Double stitched black canvas hook loop." class="object-cover object-center">
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="bg-white pb-16 sm:pb-24">
    <div class="relative sm:py-16">
      <div aria-hidden="true" class="hidden sm:block">
        <div class="absolute inset-y-0 left-0 w-1/2 rounded-r-3xl bg-gray-50"></div>
        <svg class="absolute top-8 left-1/2 -ml-3" width="404" height="392" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 404 392">
          <defs>
            <pattern id="8228f071-bcee-4ec8-905a-2a059a2cc4fb" x="0" y="0" width="20" height="20" patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse">
              <rect x="0" y="0" width="4" height="4" class="text-gray-200" fill="currentColor" />
            </pattern>
          </defs>
          <rect width="404" height="392" fill="url(#8228f071-bcee-4ec8-905a-2a059a2cc4fb)" />
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-md px-4 sm:max-w-3xl sm:px-6 lg:max-w-7xl lg:px-8">
        <div class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-tr from-purple-600 to-indigo-600 px-6 py-10 shadow-xl sm:px-12 sm:py-20">
          <div aria-hidden="true" class="absolute inset-0 -mt-72 sm:-mt-32 md:mt-0">
            <svg class="absolute inset-0 h-full w-full" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid slice" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 1463 360">
              <path class="text-purple-500 text-opacity-40" fill="currentColor" d="M-82.673 72l1761.849 472.086-134.327 501.315-1761.85-472.086z" />
              <path class="text-purple-700 text-opacity-40" fill="currentColor" d="M-217.088 544.086L1544.761 72l134.327 501.316-1761.849 472.086z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="relative">
            <div class="sm:text-center">
              <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-4xl">Join Continuous Excellence</h2>
              <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg text-purple-200">If you enjoyed our method to creating products, subscribe to our newsletter to get notified when we make more content!</p>
            </div>
            <form action="#" class="mt-12 sm:mx-auto sm:flex sm:max-w-lg">
              <div class="min-w-0 flex-1">
                <label for="cta-email" class="sr-only">Email address</label>
                <input id="cta-email" type="email" class="block w-full rounded-md border border-transparent px-5 py-3 text-base text-gray-900 placeholder-gray-500 shadow-sm focus:border-transparent focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-white focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-offset-indigo-600" placeholder="Enter your email">
              </div>
              <div class="mt-4 sm:mt-0 sm:ml-3">
                <button type="submit" class="block w-full rounded-md border border-transparent bg-purple-500 px-5 py-3 text-base font-medium text-white shadow hover:bg-purple-400 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-white focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-offset-indigo-600 sm:px-10">Notify me</button>
              </div>
            </form>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Main>